# Syllabus Pipeline UI Rules

## Feature Context
PDF upload → tree viewer → tutorial generation → MCQ generation → exam builder.
User selects AI providers (single or multi-agent) at each generation step.
Spec: @docs/features/SYLLABUS_PIPELINE.md

## AI Provider Selector (Reusable Component)
- MUST be reusable across syllabus, question generator, and future AI features
- Two modes: single-select (RadioGroup) and multi-select (Checkbox)
- "Use All" toggle selects all providers simultaneously
- Show estimated cost per provider (from constants, not API call)
- Persist user's last selection in TanStack Query cache
- Props: `mode`, `onSelect`, `defaultProviders`, `compact`

## Tree Viewer Pattern
- Use recursive component for rendering tree nodes
- State in Zustand: expandedNodes (Set<string>), selectedNodes (Set<string>)
- Fetch full tree in one call (getTree), build hierarchy client-side
- Virtualize if tree has 200+ nodes (@tanstack/react-virtual)
- Keyboard nav: arrow keys to navigate, Enter to expand/collapse, Space to select

## Status Tracking UX
- Poll `getStatus` during processing (refetchInterval: 2000)
- Show step-by-step progress: uploaded → extracting → parsing → done
- On "generating" states: show provider-specific progress if multi-agent
- Optimistic updates: mark node as "generating" immediately on button click

## Tutorial Display
- Render structured JSONB content as rich formatted sections
- Definitions: highlighted card with term in bold
- Formulas: rendered in monospace or MathJax if available
- Mnemonics: distinctive styling (callout box)
- Provider attribution: subtle tag on sections in multi-agent mode
- "Regenerate" button to create new version (preserves old)

## MCQ Review Flow
- Generated MCQs appear in a review list
- Each question: accept (✓), reject (✗), edit (✏) buttons
- Edit opens inline form with all fields editable
- Bulk actions: "Accept All", "Reject All"
- Save accepted → creates entries in questions + tutorial_questions tables
- Toast on save success with count
